
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Department {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -rooms: Set<Room>
}

class Room {
  -id: int
  -number: String
  -beds: Set<Bed>
}

class Bed {
  -id: int
  -bedNumber: String
  -category: Category
  -isOccupied: boolean
}

class Category {
  -id: int
  -type: String (RH, RNH, SF)
  -pricePerDay: double
}

class Inhabitant {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -registrationDate: Date
  -waitingListPosition: int
  -stays: Set<Stay>
  -abilitiesAssessment: AbilitiesAssessment
}

class Stay {
  -id: int
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date (nullable)
  -status: String (active, suspended, ended)
  -category: Category
  -bed: Bed
  -invoices: Set<Invoice>
}

class AbilitiesAssessment {
  -id: int
  -assessmentDate: Date
  -needsForHelp: Map<String, Level> (eating, dressing, personal care)
  -recommendedCategory: Category
}

class WaitingListEntry {
  -id: int
  -inhabitant: Inhabitant
  -category: Category
  -registrationDate: Date
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -invoiceDate: Date
  -amountDue: double
  -amountPaid: double
  -status: String (unpaid, paid, partially_paid)
  -stay: Stay
}

class PaymentEvent {
  -id: int
  -paymentDate: Date
  -amount: double
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class CreditNote {
  -id: int
  -issueDate: Date
  -amount: double
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class RegistrationProcess {
  -id: int
  -inhabitant: Inhabitant
  -registrationDate: Date
  -completed: boolean
}

class Proposal {
  -id: int
  -proposedDate: Date
  -status: String (pending, accepted, refused)
  -inhabitant: Inhabitant
  -bed: Bed
  -category: Category
}

class IntakeProcess {
  -id: int
  -inhabitant: Inhabitant
  -intakeDate: Date
  -validatedCategory: Category
}

' Relationships
Department "1" --> "0..*" Room
Room "1" --> "0..*" Bed
Bed "1" --> "1" Category
Inhabitant "1" --> "0..*" Stay
Inhabitant "1" --> "1" AbilitiesAssessment
Inhabitant "1" --> "0..*" WaitingListEntry
Stay "1" --> "0..*" Invoice
Invoice "1" --> "0..*" PaymentEvent
Invoice "1" --> "0..*" CreditNote
Proposal "1" --> "1" Inhabitant
Proposal "1" --> "1" Bed
Proposal "1" --> "1" Category
RegistrationProcess "1" --> "1" Inhabitant
IntakeProcess "1" --> "1" Inhabitant
IntakeProcess "1" --> "1" Category
WaitingListEntry "1" --> "1" Category
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Department`**, **`Room`**, and **`Bed`** form a hierarchical structure representing the physical layout.
- **`Category`** defines the type of stay and its associated price.
- **`Inhabitant`** is the main entity, with multiple **`Stay`** instances, an **`AbilitiesAssessment`**, and entries in the **`WaitingListEntry`**.
- **`Stay`** includes billing information via **`Invoice`**, which tracks payments and possible refunds via **`PaymentEvent`** and **`CreditNote`**.
- **`WaitingListEntry`** manages the waiting list logic, where inhabitants are queued based on registration date.
- **`Proposal`** represents the assignment of a bed to an inhabitant from the waiting list.
- **`IntakeProcess`** formalizes the acceptance and validation of a stay after proposal.

---

